01:01.727 --> 01:03.728
Oh, come on, just because
I have to wake up early

01:03.813 --> 01:05.230
doesn't mean you
should suffer.

01:05.313 --> 01:06.435
Well, you know
what they say.

01:06.482 --> 01:08.549
The couple
that wakes together...

01:08.601 --> 01:10.985
Bakes together?

01:11.053 --> 01:14.055
- Stays together.
- Yeah, that doesn't rhyme.

01:14.106 --> 01:16.241
You're ridiculous.

01:18.911 --> 01:20.895
Oh, my God.
That's amazing.

01:20.946 --> 01:22.563
I know.

01:22.615 --> 01:23.832
You're amazing.

01:23.899 --> 01:25.834
I know.

01:31.540 --> 01:34.459
You have no intention of
letting me go to work, do you?

01:34.543 --> 01:39.380
There once was a girl
from Nantucket.

01:39.432 --> 01:42.217
I love you.

01:42.268 --> 01:43.584
Oh, that doesn't rhyme,
you know?

01:43.636 --> 01:44.936
What are you,
the rhyming police now?

01:45.020 --> 01:47.305
- You started it.
- And I'm gonna finish it.

01:47.389 --> 01:49.691
I love you too.

02:00.820 --> 02:02.320
You look happier
than you did last night.

02:02.404 --> 02:04.322
I am.

02:06.375 --> 02:07.575
What are you doing here?

02:07.626 --> 02:09.377
I was thinking
I'd give you a ride.

02:09.443 --> 02:10.912
You just gave me a ride
last night.

02:10.963 --> 02:13.331
Yeah, this time
I thought I'd join you.

02:13.415 --> 02:15.616
Harvey,
we put in 15-hour days

02:15.668 --> 02:16.801
12 feet from each other.

02:16.886 --> 02:18.406
You really want
to go to work together?

02:18.453 --> 02:20.121
Who said anything
about work?

02:20.172 --> 02:21.506
We have breakfast
at Nougatine

02:21.590 --> 02:23.675
and an excursion to Hermes
that may or may not

02:23.759 --> 02:25.459
involve a new handbag.

02:25.511 --> 02:27.729
You've been needing
a new handbag.

02:27.796 --> 02:29.463
You can never have
too many handbags.

02:29.515 --> 02:30.836
You're a woman
after my own heart.

02:30.850 --> 02:32.684
Well, in that case...

02:35.637 --> 02:40.108
Harvey...
Why are you doing this?

02:40.159 --> 02:42.660
Donna, we've all
been through a lot.

02:42.745 --> 02:45.497
We deserve
a little celebration.

02:45.581 --> 02:48.533
Well, in that case,
you have had it pretty rough.

02:48.617 --> 02:50.835
We're gonna need to get you
more than one handbag.

02:50.920 --> 02:54.672
I wouldn't have it
any other way.

03:06.519 --> 03:07.685
Jessica.

03:07.770 --> 03:10.688
Louis, what can I do
for you?

03:10.773 --> 03:12.140
Actually, I'm not here
about me.

03:12.191 --> 03:13.274
I'm here about you.

03:13.342 --> 03:15.860
How so?

03:15.945 --> 03:20.698
Um...

03:20.783 --> 03:22.066
I want to handle
the dissolution.

03:22.151 --> 03:23.785
So this is about you.

03:23.852 --> 03:26.354
No.
Jessica...

03:26.405 --> 03:28.957
I got Ava out
when you wanted her out.

03:29.024 --> 03:30.708
I proved that I will do
whatever it takes.

03:30.793 --> 03:33.194
And what's more,
I know Darby's assets,

03:33.245 --> 03:35.246
and I will get you everything
that you have coming.

03:35.331 --> 03:36.881
I can get everything
I have coming.

03:36.966 --> 03:38.833
Maybe, but after
what Stephen Huntley

03:38.884 --> 03:41.125
and Edward Darby did, you want
to exact a pound of flesh.

03:41.136 --> 03:44.639
You want to kill them both.

03:44.706 --> 03:46.040
What's your point?

03:46.091 --> 03:48.011
My point is, is that you go
into that room angry,

03:48.060 --> 03:50.178
you're gonna have blinders on.

03:50.229 --> 03:52.180
And they're gonna lead you
any way they want you to go.

03:52.231 --> 03:54.182
I get in that room,
I'm cool as a cucumber,

03:54.233 --> 03:57.385
and I will lead whatever way
you want to go.

03:57.436 --> 04:00.221
We just got Edward Darby's
proposed formula

04:00.272 --> 04:01.889
for splitting our assets.

04:06.612 --> 04:08.830
- Son of a bitch.
- I know!

04:08.897 --> 04:10.782
He thinks he can dictate terms
after what he's done?

04:10.866 --> 04:11.899
We need to crush him.

04:11.951 --> 04:13.117
See?
Blinders.

04:13.202 --> 04:14.619
What?

04:14.703 --> 04:17.171
Louis was just suggesting
that he run the negotiations.

04:17.238 --> 04:20.291
Louis also suggested the firm
adopt a badger as a mascot.

04:20.375 --> 04:21.909
The badger is a noble
and fearsome creature,

04:21.961 --> 04:23.795
but that's not the point.
I can beat them.

04:23.879 --> 04:25.129
And the Washington Generals
think they can beat

04:25.214 --> 04:26.598
the Globetrotters,
but they're not even

04:26.682 --> 04:27.915
in the same league.

04:27.967 --> 04:29.300
My father played
for the Washington Generals.

04:29.385 --> 04:30.935
- See?
- So what are you saying?

04:31.020 --> 04:32.470
I'm not in your league?
I'm saying you and I

04:32.554 --> 04:33.921
don't even play the same sport.

04:33.973 --> 04:36.858
Harvey...enough.
And Louis has a point.

04:36.925 --> 04:38.759
You seriously want
to consider this?

04:38.811 --> 04:39.894
This is a joke.

04:39.945 --> 04:42.780
Louis, will you give us
a moment?

04:42.865 --> 04:44.866
Please?

04:47.903 --> 04:50.989
I am not a joke.

04:56.045 --> 04:57.912
You can't do that anymore.

04:57.963 --> 04:59.113
You mean make fun of Louis?

04:59.164 --> 05:00.748
It's one of life's
great pleasures.

05:00.799 --> 05:02.199
When the two of you
were colleagues,

05:02.217 --> 05:04.285
that's fair game,
but you're a name partner now,

05:04.336 --> 05:05.816
and you have to show him
some respect.

05:05.838 --> 05:07.255
I am showing him respect.

05:07.306 --> 05:10.958
I'm being dismissive
to his face.

05:11.010 --> 05:13.428
Harvey, remember Kopelman?

05:13.479 --> 05:15.513
Combovers like that
are hard to forget.

05:15.597 --> 05:18.232
When I first started here,
he and I would fight

05:18.300 --> 05:21.736
like cats and dogs every day,
toe-to-toe.

05:21.803 --> 05:23.071
Then one day
he went too far.

05:23.138 --> 05:25.323
He crossed a line,
and I'd had enough,

05:25.407 --> 05:28.809
and I went in,
and I ripped him up.

05:28.861 --> 05:30.478
You know what I did the day
after Daniel and I

05:30.529 --> 05:32.697
took over the firm?

05:32.781 --> 05:36.984
I went to Kopelman, and I told
him how much I valued him.

05:38.454 --> 05:40.088
Kopelman never voted
against you

05:40.155 --> 05:41.822
the whole time I knew him.

05:41.874 --> 05:43.708
Exactly.

05:43.792 --> 05:45.126
And by the way,
Louis is right.

05:45.177 --> 05:48.296
Jessica, it's one thing for me
to show Louis respect.

05:48.347 --> 05:50.932
But you want to put me
on the sidelines for him?

05:50.999 --> 05:52.383
No.

05:52.468 --> 05:54.769
I'm gonna put him in
at quarterback,

05:54.836 --> 05:57.021
then snap the ball to you.

05:57.106 --> 06:00.892
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

06:00.976 --> 06:04.345
♪ get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

06:04.396 --> 06:07.398
♪ everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

06:07.483 --> 06:11.018
♪ everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

06:11.070 --> 06:14.021
♪ living in a beehive,
I don't mind ♪

06:14.073 --> 06:17.909
♪ me and missy so early busy,
busy making money ♪

